<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="256" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1230,1509]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">
Distribution: Indian records: Meghalaya. Global records: 
<collectingCountry box="[835,892,1303,1329]" name="Laos" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Laos</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[910,1019,1303,1329]" name="Myanmar" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tindale, N. B." box="[1039,1198,1302,1329]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="157 - 197" refId="ref12496" refString="Tindale, N. B. (1958) Revision of the ghost moths (Lepidoptera Homoneura, family Hepialidae). Part VII. Records of the South Australian Museum, 13, 157 - 197." type="journal article" year="1958">Tindale 1958</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Grehan, J. R. &amp; Ismavel, V. A." pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="9940 - 9955" refId="ref8690" refString="Grehan, J. R. &amp; Ismavel, V. A. (2017) Forest ghost moth fauna of northeastern India (Lepidoptera: Hepialidae: Endoclita, Palpifer, and Hepialiscus). Journal of Threatened Taxa, 9 (3), 9940 - 9955. https: // doi. org / 10.11609 / jott. 3030.9.3.9940 - 9955" type="journal article" year="2017">Grehan &amp; Ismavel 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="256" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1230,1509]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">
Note: 
<taxonomicName box="[222,409,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Phassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auratus">
<emphasis box="[222,409,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Phassus auratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was transferred to 
<taxonomicName box="[632,741,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Endoclita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[632,741,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Endoclita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tindale, N. B." box="[786,954,1375,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="15 - 46" refId="ref12420" refString="Tindale, N. B. (1941) Revision of the ghost moths (Lepidoptera Homoneura, family Hepialidae). Part IV. Records of the South Australian Museum, 7, 15 - 46." type="journal article" year="1941">Tindale (1941)</bibRefCitation>
who also mentioned the locality as Khasi Hills which was under 
<collectingRegion box="[459,535,1411,1437]" country="India" name="Assam" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Assam</collectingRegion>
previously. From 21 
<superScript attach="left" box="[772,783,1411,1425]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">st</superScript>
January, 1972, Khasi Hills fall under the state of 
<collectingRegion country="India" name="Meghalaya" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Meghalaya</collectingRegion>
. Though 
<bibRefCitation author="Grehan, J. R. &amp; Mielke, C. G. C. &amp; Basu, D. N. &amp; Pawar, U. &amp; Ismavel, V. A. &amp; Rawlins, J. E. &amp; Kunte, K." box="[352,579,1447,1473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref8927" refString="Grehan, J. R., Mielke, C. G. C., Basu, D. N., Pawar, U., Ismavel, V. A., Rawlins, J. E. &amp; Kunte, K. (2022) A new species of Endoclita C. &amp; R. Felder, 1874 ghost moth from Karimganj district of Assam, India, with comments on the genus in Northeastern India, and clarification of E. signifer (Walker, 1856) (Lepidoptera: Hepialidae). ZooNova, 16, 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="2022">
Grehan 
<emphasis box="[441,490,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">et al</emphasis>
. (2022)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the distribution from 
<collectingRegion box="[948,1027,1447,1473]" country="India" name="Assam" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Assam</collectingRegion>
, it is not correct. Hence, in this catalogue the distribution changed with proper justification.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
